The paper deals with image synthesis, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a generative adversarial network (GAN) with a novel architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of bounding boxes and class labels in the image lattice suggests a possible connection to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the experiments involve datasets of natural images, which could also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
